# Alalā Core Standards

You are working on Alalā — physics-first AI on Apple Silicon M4 maximizing Intelligence per Joule.

## Required reading order
1. @docs/Project_Index_Alalā.md
2. @docs/AI_Coder_Rules_Guidelines_Alalā.md
3. @docs/OSLab_Program_Board.md (current status)

## Code and doc discipline
- Minimal, focused diffs — do not refactor unrelated code.
- Match existing naming, types, and patterns in surrounding files.
- Never commit placeholder stubs (`Content of X.md`, `Binary zip content`, etc.).
- Run `./verify.sh` before every commit; it must pass.
- Update @docs/OSLab_Program_Board.md after significant tasks.

## Physics and safety constraints
- SRAM budget: keep hot working sets under ~28–30 MB when possible.
- ANE-first for compute-bound ops; minimize Python orchestration in hot paths.
- Respect thermal limits; treat temperature as a scheduling variable.
- Self-improvement requires HCA Impact Statement + positive marginal IPJ.

## Communication
- Be precise and technical; include numbers (IPJ, joules, tokens/s, utilization %) when relevant.
- State assumptions; flag risks and unknowns.
- Escalate to human for >10% IPJ impact or architectural decisions.
- Follow @.cursor/rules/no-ai-markers.mdc: no em dashes, no stock AI phrasing in user-facing text.

